WorldStage Newsonline– National Assembly (NASS) workers under the auspices of the Parliamentary Staff Association of Nigeria (PASAN) on Friday said that the planned industrial action would commence on Dec. 18 as earlier scheduled if their demands were not met as promised. The aggrieved staff had on Dec. 4, picketed the assembly complex, grounding legislative proceedings in both houses for the day. The Chairman of PASAN, Comrade Musa Bature said at a press briefing in Abuja that the picketing which started on Tuesday was to last till Thursday, Dec. 6 as a prelude and warning signal to a proposed total strike action billed to begin on Dec. 18, but for the intervention of NASS leadership..